I ordered through grubhub today and received my order in a sauce-soaked bag. All of the food packaging was covered in sauce and sticky. One of my drinks was missing, no utensils, napkins, or packaged sauces given like most restaurants. I also ordered the cheese and meat wontons (8) and received 6. I was told that in order to receive a refund I'd have to give back all of the food to the restaurant. Wont be ordering from here or using grabhub again.

Great asian-fusion carryout joint. The folks are super friendly, the food is tasty, and it's ready quick.  They're not overpriced, have lunch and dinner combos, and the portion size is good. The Singapore noodles are the best I've had in bmore. The hot and sour soup is perfection. I'll be honest, I don't like every single dish, but the ones I have are excellent. If you don't mess up Hunan chicken you're solid in my opinion, and they do it right.

Good food. The delivery drivers are excellent! I order through Grubhub and they send their own drivers. They always come to my door instead of just to the lobby of the building. They are always on time as well.

Excellent sushi, we've tried it twice and we're not disappointed, not the usual all fried or tempura roll, it is flavored, fresh and various. Really enjoying and definitely the only place we order now because all other places around FedHill are not rivalising.

Tasty food prepared quickly, the Dynamite roll is my favorite!!!!

One of my Baltimore Associates highly recommended this restaurant.  I've been looking for good Chinese food in Baltimore for years and decided to order food to go.  This was a major disappointment.  I ordered a large wonton soup.  The wonton dough was sooo thick and whatever it was stuffed with made me dump all of them after a first bite.  Wonton should be translucent with recognizable meat, seafood or veggies.  The shrimp rolls were tasteless.  My husband said his Green Curry Chicken was  okay, but I found it to be barely satisfactory.  If you're a traveling soul, as we are, your expectations of food differs from people who have not had the experience of traveling to locations where food quality is a priority all the time.  I will never eat there again, nor could I in good conscience recommend it.
Standard carry out food, nothing special. The customer service sucks!
Loved it!!
First time eating and the food was delicious great service. Didn’t like too much the hot and sour soup.

Just ordered from here. All of the food came and it tasted fine. The crab rangoon was delicious (which is why this is 2 stars and not 1). However the drunken noodle was only mildly spicy when I specifically ordered very spicy. They provided no utensils: neither chopsticks nor forks. The delivery person ignored my comment to buzz in and instead waited across the street until I came to the door.

Oh my goodness, I will officially be ordering my Asian takeout EXCLUSIVELY from this place. Three maki rolls for $12??? My entire order was the three roll special, vegetable spring rolls, egg drop soup, and chicken with vegetables. The total for my order was just a bit over $36 and that's WITH a 20% tip!! Love it!
Great sushi at an amazing price. Excellent service. I eat here at least twice a week. #bestinbmore
Good selection of traditional Chinese cuisine
Try the inner harbor roll and pay the up charge for jumbo lump crabmeat.
I love this spot! My all time fave is the Calamari.

When my husband and I lived in Little Italy a year ago, we used to order from this spot ALL THE TIME! I was working nearby downtown this month and decided to give our trusty spot a call for lunch. It is the best Chinese carryout we've had in Baltimore. Always fast, always tasty and never disappointing! It's not fancy at all, but they are very consistent. It was just as good this time as it was last time.

The best chinese food unless you order a meal with beef.  All the chinese stores no longer use real beef.  Not sure what they use, but the texture , taste and look is not like beef.  Parking is an issue.
This place is great! Order sushi and orange chicken and everything came looking great and tasting even better. Definitely reccemond it!
Good food and service

Best Chinese Food in the city - HANDS DOWN. I have been ordering from here for 4 years now and I am never disappointed. The food is fresh and made exactly how I like it. The steamed dumplings are my favorite - I've ordered from other places around the city when Asian Harbor is closed and it's clear no one else knows how to make a proper dumpling or the proper sauce that goes with it. The lunch combos are also perfectly portioned and priced. I LOVE ASIAN HARBOR.

I write this with regret. I have been a loyal customer of Asian Harbor for around 2 years. Tonight, I had a bug or spider in my won ton soup. They offered to refund the soup and remake the order. The last thing I want is MORE food from a place that already served us bugs. It totally grossed my family out and we tossed the rest of the food. I understand businesses needing to protect themselves from jerks who try to rip them off, but I am not one of those people, and my Order Up order history can prove it. I'm very disappointed with how they dealt with this situation. I will never order from them again and I will recommend against them to everyone in the neighborhood.
Fresh and made to order Sushi.  Try the fried Salt & Pepper Calamari. . .excellent!

So far I've tried the Lunch Menu for the Wing's and Fried Vegetable Rice. The Wing's was a nice size, color great which means the Cooking Grease is clean, tasted pretty good. I haven't tried the Rice yet

The quality of the food as of Jan 21 2017 has taken a huge step up from before. Orange chicken was huge chunks with just enough breaking. Lo mein which was flavorless is now packed with flavor and tastes great as leftovers the next day.
I became VERY ill after eating here.  I will not being ordering from here again.

Please don't order from here. I waited over an hour and a half for my food. The driver called to let me know he was here but actually he was at the wrong place. He never called me back and when I called him to see where he was at he never answered. I had to call the restaurant to see what happened and they said they will send him back but by this time, I am upset and hungry so I had to call another place to get something to eat. They are unprofessional and don't care about their customers. I will spend my money elsewhere.

Tonight was my first and last time trying Asian Harbor.  I ordered Hunan Tofu, and the tofu was inedible; the outer breading was a soggy slimy mess.  The sauce was extremely thick and gelatinous and covered everything in globs.  I am very disappointed.
